<paragraph id="8B8136F9FF9CC933FF32FC46FD4CFBB5" blockId="61.[151,1436,972,1143]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9CC933FF32FC46FF58FC25" bold="true" box="[151,214,972,998]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">Note.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAF4B08FF9CC933FF79FC46FEF8FC25" author="Simon, E." box="[220,374,972,998]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="860 - 890" refId="ref51914" refString="Simon, E. (1898) On the spiders of the island of St Vincent. III. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 65, 860 - 890. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1898. tb 01390. x" type="journal article" year="1898">Simon (1898)</bibRefCitation>
originally described both males and females of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3E4D7AFF9CC933FC2DFC47FBC6FC25" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Jäger" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[904,1096,973,998]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Meri" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanctivincenti" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9CC933FC2DFC47FBC6FC25" box="[904,1096,973,998]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">M. sanctivincenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94AEAEBFF9CC933FBE8FC46FB43FC25" bold="true" box="[1101,1229,972,998]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2795790FF9CC933FBE8FC46FB43FC25" box="[1101,1229,972,998]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
However, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAF4B08FF9CC933FAE0FC47FF6CFBC8" author="Roewer, C. F." pageId="61" pageNumber="62" refId="ref51689" refString="Roewer, C. F. (1955) Katalog der Araneae von 1758 bis 1940, bzw. 1954. 2. Band, Abt. a (Lycosaeformia, Dionycha [excl. Salticiformia]). Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique Bruxelles, Bruxelles, 923 pp." type="book" year="1955">Roewer (1955)</bibRefCitation>
lists only females decribed. In addition, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAF4B08FF9CC933FD13FC7BFCFEFBC9" author="Jager, P." box="[694,880,1008,1035]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 119" refId="ref50999" refString="Jager, P. (2020) The spider genus Olios Walckenaer, 1837 (Araneae: Sparassidae) - Part 1: species groups, diagnoses, identification keys, distribution maps and revision of the argelasius -, coenobitus - and auricomis - groups. Zootaxa, 4866 (1), 1 - 119. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4866.1.1" type="journal article" year="2020">Jäger (2020: 94)</bibRefCitation>
states that, although a type series was located at NHM, it included only female specimens. Since the description does not allow the proper identification and the location of the male types is unknown, we are designating the female specimens deposited in NHM as 
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF9CC933FAA2FBB2FAE0FB91" box="[1287,1390,1080,1106]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">lectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="5485885BFF9CC933FF32FBD6FEBFFBB5" box="[151,305,1116,1142]" pageId="61" pageNumber="62">paralectotype</typeStatus>
, thus fixing the name to the female.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
